solution:
Remove the invalid/unsupported region codes via PowerShell:
For XJ/XE/XS: Set-HostedContentFilterPolicy -Identity 'Policy Name' -RegionBlockList @{Remove='XJ','XE','XS'}
For SS/EH: Set-HostedContentFilterPolicy -Identity 'Policy Name' -RegionBlockList @{Remove='SS','EH'}
Capture a HAR/Fiddler trace first to identify exactly which codes are in the error message. Reference engineering bug: https://o365exchange.visualstudio.com/IP%20Engineering/_workitems/edit/6740044

Use PowerShell to add trusted senders as a workaround:
Set-AntiPhishPolicy -Identity 'Standard Preset Security Policy' -ExcludedSenders @{Add='trustedaddress@externalcontoso.com'}
Replace the email address with the desired trusted sender. Escalate the case referencing Bug 6646002 to help get traction on the UI fix.
